  "imageCount": 3,
  "body": "<figure>\n\n\n<img src=\"https://images.squarespace-cdn.com/content/v1/5dd0ae59b4b4b35c07faf907/1597737101646-YXAGC7DXB4GZXWHULX5Y/8a-big%2Bjuicy%2Bcreative%2Blife.jpeg\"/>\n\n\n</figure>\n\n\n<p>This was one of those quotes I saw on Pinterest and had no idea how it would turn out since it's a bit long. I decided to write it out and this was my first attempt. I don't often get it right on the first try, and this was a perfect example of that. I ended up running out of room at the bottom and had to place Anne Lamott's name on the left side. And I also got a random paint splotch on it. But instead of starting over, I decided it would be better to add more splotches and just go with it. I mean, isn't that what the quote is trying to tell us in the first place?</p>\n\n\n\n\n\n\n<figure>\n\n\n<img src=\"https://images.squarespace-cdn.com/content/v1/5dd0ae59b4b4b35c07faf907/1597737144497-QGAFR6WCML1T1L49B8J0/8b-big%2Bjuicy%2Bcreative%2Blife.jpeg\"/>\n\n\n</figure>\n\n\n\n<figure>\n\n\n<img src=\"https://images.squarespace-cdn.com/content/v1/5dd0ae59b4b4b35c07faf907/1597737165335-V1JYRDBK5BF5G8JPV32V/image-asset.jpeg\"/>\n\n\n<figcaption>\n<p>Hope to continue spreading more motivation for each of your Mondays this year using <a href=\"http://www.michaels.com/artists-loft-fundamentals-watercolor-pan-set/10122060.html#q=watercolor&amp;start=2\">this watercolor set from Michaels</a> and a brush that says Royal 2 on it (can’t remember where it’s from, sorry!). I also found some alternative watercolor options <a href=\"http://www.amazon.com/gp/product/B00114RIIQ/ref=as_li_tl?ie=UTF8&amp;amp;camp=1789&amp;amp;creative=390957&amp;amp;creativeASIN=B00114RIIQ&amp;amp;linkCode=as2&amp;amp;tag=wwwamytangeri-20&amp;amp;linkId=SEL4W2XO57Q&amp;lt;a%20href=\">here</a> and <a href=\"http://www.amazon.com/gp/product/B0019IKY58/ref=as_li_tl?ie=UTF8&amp;amp;camp=1789&amp;amp;creative=390957&amp;amp;creativeASIN=B0019IKY58&amp;amp;linkCode=as2&amp;amp;tag=wwwamytangeri-20&amp;amp;linkId=Y4TM3YCBZ74FFNPO\">here</a>. If you have a favorite quote – snarky, silly, or simple in its’ wisdom, please share in the comments!</p>\n</figcaption>\n</figure>"
